00:01:22.880 --> 00:01:24.980
are counted differently.

00:01:24.980 --> 00:01:26.960
But you can organize
the field theory

00:01:26.960 --> 00:01:29.240
using equations of motion
so that these are just

00:01:29.240 --> 00:01:34.220
local operators with
spatial derivatives.

00:01:34.220 --> 00:01:36.675
So you basically deal with
the time derivatives once

00:01:36.675 --> 00:01:39.050
and for all, and you could
always use equations of motion

00:01:39.050 --> 00:01:40.950
to eliminate them there.

00:01:40.950 --> 00:01:44.690
