00:03:22.880 --> 00:03:24.350
And then the rest
of the couplings

00:03:24.350 --> 00:03:27.480
are treated perturbatively,
the higher derivative term.

00:03:27.480 --> 00:03:32.060
So a term, c 2, which
comes with grad squared,

00:03:32.060 --> 00:03:33.590
and that gives this
extra p squared.

00:03:33.590 --> 00:03:36.242
And the numerator here gets
treated perturbatively,

00:03:36.242 --> 00:03:38.450
and there's this term, and
then there's higher terms.

00:03:38.450 --> 00:03:40.790
And that's how we could
organize this theory,

00:03:40.790 --> 00:03:44.450
and this sums up all
these powers of a times p,

00:03:44.450 --> 00:03:47.940
these denominators that
I'm showing you there.

